author: Javier Blas, Angelina Rascouet, Nayla Razzouk
description: At first glance, OPEC’s cuts haven’t worked -- global oil inventories remain well above normal levels. But the policy’s made a difference where it really counts: juicing the coffers of finance ministries from Baghdad to Caracas.
title: OPEC Wants to Carry on Pumping Less and Earning More
